                      },
                      "locus": "ff. 148r-205r",
                      "excerpt": [
                        {
                          "type": {
                            "id": "incipit",
                            "label": "Incipit"
                          },
                          "locus": "f. 148r",
                          "as_written": "التسبحه الاولى على وزن معيناً وساترا صار لى للخلاص",
                          "translation": [
                            "The first hymn in meter: My helper and shelter He became for me in salvation…"
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": {
                            "id": "explicit",
                            "label": "Explicit"
                          },
                          "locus": "ff. 204v-205r",
                          "as_written": "وبك ترحص كل محنه وتسبى المحاربين اياها. وتتبع المطيع. والسبح لله دايماً",
                          "translation": [
                            "And with You, every trial is made to flee, the warriors are taken prisoner, and the obedient are attended to. And glory to God always"
                          ]
                        }
                      ],
                      "note": [
                        "This canon is further subdivided into nine metrical hymns (or odes), in which there is also further rubrication for various parts of the hymns."
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "work": {
                        "desc_title": "Prayer spoken before receiving the Holy Eucharist",
                        "genre": [
                          {
                            "id": "prayers",
                            "label": "Prayers"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      "as_written": "هذه الصَلاه تقال قبل اخذ القربان المقدسَ (f. 205v)",
                      "locus": "ff. 205v-207v",
                      "excerpt": [
                        {
                          "type": {
                            "id": "incipit",
                            "label": "Incipit"
                          },
                          "locus": "f. 205v",
                          "as_written": "قدوسَ قدوسَ قدوسَ انت يالله قدسَ نفسَی وجسَدي وروحى",
                          "translation": [
                            "Holy, holy, holy are you, O God. Sanctify my soul, my body, and my spirit…"
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": {
                            "id": "explicit",
                            "label": "Explicit"
                          },
                          "locus": "f. 207v",
                          "as_written": "بك سُررت ان تغذینی انا الخاطى على مايدتك المحييه الغير مايته الذي اسالك ان تحفظ",
                          "translation": [
                            "Rather, I was pleased that You would feed me, a sinner, at Your life-giving and immortal table which I ask that You would sustain…"
                          ]
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "work": {
                        "desc_title": "Teaching from the treatise of Anba Stephen of the Thebaid",
                        "genre": [
                          {
                            "id": "theological-works",
                            "label": "Theological works"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      "locus": "ff. 208r-215v",
                      "excerpt": [
                        {
                          "type": {
                            "id": "incipit",
                            "label": "Incipit"
                          },
                          "locus": "f. 208r",
                          "as_written": "الان يا ابني قبل كل شى اكفر بالعالم وابتعد من ارضك ومن جنسك",
                          "translation": [
                            "Now, my son, before all else depart from the world and renounce your country and your kin…"
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": {
                            "id": "subscription",
                            "label": "Subscription"
                          },
                          "locus": "f. 215v",
                          "as_written": "تكون اعمالك ذكيه لكى يستجيب للله منك عاجلاً",
                          "translation": [
                            "...let your deeds be redolent that God may respond to you sooner..."
                          ]
                        }
                      ]
                    }
